00:15:05.320 --> 00:15:17.320
We could have paid the full, but because we weren't earning that much, we went off of it then, so it was half a stamp we were paying then at that time.

00:15:17.320 --> 00:15:19.320
Did you have to clock in?

00:15:19.320 --> 00:15:21.320
Oh yes, we had to clock in, yes.

00:15:21.320 --> 00:15:22.320
And clock out?

00:15:22.320 --> 00:15:23.320
And clock out, yes.

00:15:23.320 --> 00:15:28.320
So when you clocked out, did you stop working straight away, or did you finish a job when you were?

00:15:28.320 --> 00:15:40.320
Oh no, well we had to finish a job first, and we had to get them out, they gave us a target to get out, and we had to do that target, otherwise you wouldn't have your bonus sort of thing, you know.

00:15:40.320 --> 00:15:46.320
So we had to do that before we could clock out anyhow, but we did manage it anyhow.

00:15:46.320 --> 00:15:48.320
So it was so much a day exactly?

00:15:48.320 --> 00:15:54.320
Oh yes, we had to get our target out, they'd tell us how many we were supposed to get out, we got to try and get that out.

00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:56.320
Did you remember how much that was?

00:15:56.320 --> 00:15:57.320
No, I couldn't.

00:15:57.320 --> 00:15:58.320
No.

00:15:58.320 --> 00:16:01.320
And then the bonus was on top of your wage, was it?

00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:06.320
Yes, if we had the bonus we'd go on top of our wage then, see, to build it up a bit then, yes.

00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:08.320
And when were you paid?

00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:11.320
On a Friday, we paid da da da.

00:16:11.320 --> 00:16:12.320
In cash?

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:15.320
Oh yes, yes, we were preferred in cash.

00:16:15.320 --> 00:16:20.320
And do you ever go to the office, or how were you paid?

00:16:20.320 --> 00:16:23.320
No, they bring it out, they bring it around.

00:16:23.320 --> 00:16:30.320
I don't know if the supervisors, they bring them around for you, in their packets ready for you.

00:16:30.320 --> 00:16:34.320
Were you given pay rises, you know? Do you remember if the money went up at all?

00:16:37.320 --> 00:16:43.320
No, I don't think, it was only that the bonus was making it more in the way.

00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:46.320
If you can get the bonus out.

00:16:46.320 --> 00:16:52.320
How many years did you work in Fisher Price before moving to Metoey?

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:54.320
I don't know.

00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:58.320
Were you talking about four, five, six years or more?

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:01.320
No, it couldn't have been that. Say three years.

00:17:01.320 --> 00:17:06.320
It was three years, I can't remember when they finished there.

00:17:06.320 --> 00:17:10.320
So did you have holidays from the work?

00:17:10.320 --> 00:17:13.320
No, I don't think we ever bothered with holidays.

00:17:13.320 --> 00:17:15.320
Is that because you were part-time perhaps?

00:17:15.320 --> 00:17:16.320
Yeah, could be, yeah.

00:17:16.320 --> 00:17:20.320
Did you work in the holidays then, or did you have the holidays off, do you remember?

00:17:20.320 --> 00:17:22.320
No, I can't remember.

00:17:22.320 --> 00:17:26.320
No, I think we were working in school holidays.

00:17:26.320 --> 00:17:33.320
Because my children were looking after the small ones then, I think we were working on school holidays.

00:17:33.320 --> 00:17:36.320
So we were.

00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:39.320
Right. Did you enjoy working there?

00:17:39.320 --> 00:17:44.320
Yes, they were good and they were good. Crowd there, you know, right, those two them, yeah.

00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:49.320
Did you meet up with them, you know, socially at all?

00:17:49.320 --> 00:17:57.320
Oh yes, we went out for a meal and a drink sort of thing on Christmas time and we all enjoyed, yeah.

00:17:57.320 --> 00:18:00.320
Don't ask me where we went, I can't remember.

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:04.320
But there was a load of us and we really enjoyed it, yeah.

00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:06.320
How many, it was women mostly then?

00:18:06.320 --> 00:18:09.320
Oh yes, women mostly, yes.

00:18:09.320 --> 00:18:11.320
Were you supervised by a woman or by a man?

00:18:11.320 --> 00:18:14.320
By the woman, by the woman, yeah.

00:18:14.320 --> 00:18:16.320
Would you have liked to have been a supervisor?

00:18:16.320 --> 00:18:20.320
No, too much responsibility on that, no.

00:18:20.320 --> 00:18:23.320
Do you remember the supervisor though, was she quite strict?

00:18:23.320 --> 00:18:27.320
No, they were good, no, no, they were very good to us.

00:18:27.320 --> 00:18:33.320
They weren't nasty and nothing like that. If we'd done anything wrong they'd just tell us where we'd gone wrong.

00:18:33.320 --> 00:18:36.320
Was it, no, you see it all in the factory?

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:41.320
It was a little bit, not much, mind you, it was, because there's machines there as well, like see.

00:18:41.320 --> 00:18:44.320
So it was a bit, but not so much as all that.

00:18:44.320 --> 00:18:48.320
And did you, were you allowed to talk when you were working or did you have to?

00:18:48.320 --> 00:18:52.320
No, we could talk, yeah, we could talk, as long as we'd done the work.

00:18:52.320 --> 00:18:57.320
As long as it was going out they don't care. Yeah, we were talking.

00:18:57.320 --> 00:19:00.320
And I know you like singing, did you sing at all as you worked?

00:19:00.320 --> 00:19:04.320
No, no, they didn't know I could sing.

00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:07.320
And was there music on at all, do you remember I think?

00:19:07.320 --> 00:19:10.320
Yeah, there was music on, but it was very cold there.

00:19:10.320 --> 00:19:14.320
It was cold in the winter there, but they did bring the machines out.

00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:20.320
I didn't know this gas, but it was very sickly and it was horrible.

00:19:20.320 --> 00:19:23.320
That's the only thing we could have is to keep us warm.

00:19:23.320 --> 00:19:29.320
And of course the summer then, they did bring us drinks around for us because it was so warm there.

00:19:29.320 --> 00:19:31.320
We had a nice summer then.

00:19:31.320 --> 00:19:36.320
And we were having free drinks then to cool us down a bit.

00:19:36.320 --> 00:19:38.320
So what drinks were they then? Squash.

00:19:38.320 --> 00:19:40.320
Squash, yeah, squash, let's see.

00:19:40.320 --> 00:19:42.320
So why was it hot then there?

00:19:42.320 --> 00:19:45.320
Well, it was glass up top as well, see.

00:19:45.320 --> 00:19:49.320
So the bed was cold and the bed was hot.

00:19:49.320 --> 00:19:53.320
What about the union then, did you come out and strike about that at all?

00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:59.320
No, I don't think so. No, I can't remember coming out and strike there.

00:19:59.320 --> 00:20:07.320
Was it in any way dangerous, you know, that the work, that you could hurt yourself at all?

00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:11.320
You were talking about your mother and the tinworks.

00:20:11.320 --> 00:20:12.320
Oh yeah, the tinworks.

00:20:12.320 --> 00:20:14.320
Was there any?

00:20:14.320 --> 00:20:16.320
Well, perhaps there could be.

00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:21.320
There were some machines, if you could watch them, yes.

00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:26.320
There were some machines that you've got to watch where your fingers and things are going.

00:20:26.320 --> 00:20:28.320
Were you hurt at all?

00:20:28.320 --> 00:20:30.320
No, that's the word, no.

00:20:30.320 --> 00:20:32.320
Was there a nurse there?

00:20:32.320 --> 00:20:36.320
Oh yes, a nurse was there, yes, a nurse was there.

00:20:36.320 --> 00:20:39.320
So what did she do then, if there were people who weren't being hurt?

00:20:39.320 --> 00:20:48.320
Well, she'd put her in her office and bandaged them up if they cut themselves or things, so they'd do things like that.

00:20:48.320 --> 00:20:52.320
Or if anybody was taken ill, they'd send them home then.

00:20:52.320 --> 00:20:54.320
So anybody was taken ill.

00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:56.320
She was there full time, was she?

00:20:56.320 --> 00:20:58.320
Yes, she was there full time, yes.

00:20:58.320 --> 00:21:03.320
What about the working day now?

00:21:03.320 --> 00:21:05.320
Trina, you're going half past nine.

00:21:05.320 --> 00:21:08.320
Did you have a break at dinnertime or what happened?

00:21:08.320 --> 00:21:11.320
Oh yes, we do have a break for dinnertime.

00:21:11.320 --> 00:21:13.320
Yes, we had breaks there.

00:21:13.320 --> 00:21:15.320
Did they have a canteen?

00:21:15.320 --> 00:21:17.320
Yes, they got a canteen there.

00:21:17.320 --> 00:21:22.320
But I was taking my own food, I was though, because I didn't care much for the canteen food there.

00:21:22.320 --> 00:21:25.320
But I was buying some sometimes.

00:21:25.320 --> 00:21:28.320
But my daughter, I was taking my own.

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:34.320
Did you have a break in the morning as well, and in the afternoon, because you were part time now?

00:21:34.320 --> 00:21:43.320
Well, we did in the summer, because it was so warm there, we were having a ten minutes break, because it was so warm in the summer.

00:21:43.320 --> 00:21:47.320
Ten minutes break in the morning and afternoon as well.

00:21:47.320 --> 00:21:54.320
That's when we was over meadow, when we were doing full time then, when we were working full time that was.

00:21:54.320 --> 00:21:56.320
But not in Fisher Price?

00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:57.320
No.

00:21:57.320 --> 00:22:01.320
Did the women smoke at all?

00:22:01.320 --> 00:22:02.320
Oh yes.

00:22:02.320 --> 00:22:05.320
What happened if they smoked? Do they smoke in the factory?

00:22:05.320 --> 00:22:10.320
Oh no, they didn't smoke in the factory. They had to go outside to smoke in the factories.

00:22:10.320 --> 00:22:15.320
Or in the canteen then, because it was those days.

00:22:15.320 --> 00:22:19.320
Outside they had to do it, they don't do it inside.

00:22:19.320 --> 00:22:21.320
You didn't smoke yourself?

00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:22.320
No.

00:22:22.320 --> 00:22:24.320
But the toilets, were there enough toilets there?

00:22:24.320 --> 00:22:26.320
Yes, nice toilets there.

00:22:26.320 --> 00:22:30.320
So there were men now, there were men working in the factories?

00:22:30.320 --> 00:22:31.320
Oh yes, there were men working.

00:22:31.320 --> 00:22:34.320
What were they doing?

00:22:34.320 --> 00:22:47.320
Well, they were taking the toys and the trolleys and things, and I think some of them, because in the Metjoys they had paid things there to the wealthy to pay some of the toys, so mostly they were there.

00:22:47.320 --> 00:22:52.320
But I think some of the women had been doing that as well, as I was told.

00:22:52.320 --> 00:22:54.320
And some of the women were doing it as well.

00:22:54.320 --> 00:22:55.320
Right.

00:22:55.320 --> 00:22:57.320
Yes, in the paint shop there.

00:22:57.320 --> 00:23:06.320
So if the men came into the factory, went in the lines where you were, did you tease them and provoke them? Was there a banter between the women and the men?

00:23:06.320 --> 00:23:11.320
No, some of them, if we did tease some of them, yeah, they teased us back.

00:23:11.320 --> 00:23:17.320
Yeah, because they were nice men, they were very nice. Yeah, we were teasing them.

00:23:17.320 --> 00:23:18.320
What did you say to them?

00:23:18.320 --> 00:23:20.320
Oh, I can't remember.

00:23:20.320 --> 00:23:22.320
Are you not going to remember either?

00:23:22.320 --> 00:23:25.320
Oh, I can't remember what you said to them.

00:23:25.320 --> 00:23:27.320
But there was banter and fun then?

00:23:27.320 --> 00:23:29.320
Oh yes, yes, it was more or less that.

00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:33.320
Did they play any sort of tricks on new girls who came to the factory?

00:23:33.320 --> 00:23:34.320
No, they didn't.

00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:36.320
So you can't remember anything like that at all?

00:23:36.320 --> 00:23:38.320
No, they didn't do it to us any of them.

00:23:38.320 --> 00:23:40.320
They were very good to us, yeah.

00:23:40.320 --> 00:23:43.320
And often they were showing us what to do.

00:23:43.320 --> 00:23:46.320
So that's how you learnt, is you were watching others?

00:23:46.320 --> 00:23:48.320
Yeah, and they were telling us, yeah.

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:50.320
No, they weren't doing anything like that.

00:23:50.320 --> 00:23:52.320
Okay.

00:23:52.320 --> 00:23:54.320
Then you moved on to METOI.

00:23:54.320 --> 00:24:02.320
What was the difference between Fisher Price and METOI? What did you say? Was there something, did you notice a lot of difference?

00:24:02.320 --> 00:24:09.320
Oh, yeah, as you see, a lot of difference, as regards for the toys, because METOI were making more cars and things.

00:24:09.320 --> 00:24:13.320
When Fisher Price, they were making more different things.

00:24:13.320 --> 00:24:25.320
And I fancy they were easy to make then, METOI itself, because you could put little things with the cars and things like that.

00:24:25.320 --> 00:24:29.320
So what did you do in METOI? What exactly were you doing? You were on the line again?

00:24:29.320 --> 00:24:31.320
Yeah, I was on the line.

00:24:31.320 --> 00:24:33.320
What was that?

00:24:33.320 --> 00:24:35.320
Were you working on the cars?

00:24:35.320 --> 00:24:37.320
Some cars, I know.

00:24:37.320 --> 00:24:40.320
Yeah, some cars. I'm trying to remember.

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:47.320
Oh, we were doing those tops, you know, you press down, they spin.

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:49.320
Remember those?

00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:51.320
We were doing them as well.

00:24:51.320 --> 00:24:53.320
Now, something's coming to me now.

00:24:53.320 --> 00:24:55.320
We were making them as well.

00:24:55.320 --> 00:24:57.320
I can't remember what else.

00:24:57.320 --> 00:24:59.320
Those were made of metal?

00:24:59.320 --> 00:25:01.320
Yes, that was metal, that is.

00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:03.320
So we were making them there.

00:25:03.320 --> 00:25:07.320
Not only cars, we were making other things, which I can't remember.

00:25:07.320 --> 00:25:11.320
Cars we were doing and that top we were doing as well.

00:25:11.320 --> 00:25:13.320
And what else were we doing?

00:25:13.320 --> 00:25:22.320
Oh, and the roundabout, the swings on them, you know, we were doing them as well.

00:25:22.320 --> 00:25:25.320
So this was much more smaller?

00:25:25.320 --> 00:25:27.320
Yes, much smaller.

00:25:27.320 --> 00:25:32.320
Not only cars we were doing, we were doing other things as well, there in metals.

00:25:32.320 --> 00:25:34.320
So you moved around to different things?

00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:35.320
Yeah.

00:25:35.320 --> 00:25:37.320
Did you find it more for sea work?

00:25:37.320 --> 00:25:41.320
Well, it is with the little things we had to put in, yes.

00:25:41.320 --> 00:25:43.320
It was very tricky, some of them were.

00:25:43.320 --> 00:25:47.320
Did you enjoy that better? Which would you enjoy most, the Fisher Price or metal?

00:25:47.320 --> 00:25:52.320
Oh, no, I think Fisher Price was the best as it comes for toys.

00:25:52.320 --> 00:25:54.320
And as a place to work?

00:25:54.320 --> 00:25:57.320
Yes, it was good, yes, it was nice there.

00:25:57.320 --> 00:26:03.320
Well, as it was, there wasn't many there, because it was a small place, see, so.

00:26:03.320 --> 00:26:05.320
What happened then? Why did that close?

00:26:05.320 --> 00:26:09.320
I don't know, I don't know why they closed.

00:26:09.320 --> 00:26:15.320
I suppose they couldn't afford the materials or something like that.

00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:17.320
And yet they are still making them.

00:26:17.320 --> 00:26:19.320
Did the whole factory close?

00:26:19.320 --> 00:26:23.320
Yes, all of them is closed down there now.

00:26:23.320 --> 00:26:25.320
I don't know if there is anything down there now.

00:26:25.320 --> 00:26:28.320
So METOI didn't take over the Fisher Price?

00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:29.320
No.

00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:30.320
They were next door?

00:26:30.320 --> 00:26:33.320
Yeah, they were next door, see, they were already there before them.

00:26:33.320 --> 00:26:36.320
I don't know how long the Fisher Price was there, mate, I don't know.

00:26:36.320 --> 00:26:42.320
So with the METOI, sorry, with the Fisher Price, were you given any redundancy pay?

00:26:42.320 --> 00:26:48.320
How long did you, when did you hear about it and were you given any pay and what was the difference then?

00:26:48.320 --> 00:26:52.320
I can't remember, no, we didn't have redundancy from them, no.

00:26:52.320 --> 00:26:54.320
It's only from METOI we had.

00:26:56.320 --> 00:26:58.320
No, I can't remember that.

00:27:00.320 --> 00:27:04.320
So you were told that it was closing?

00:27:04.320 --> 00:27:09.320
Yeah, and we had to go over, well it's up to you if you want to go over to METOI,

00:27:09.320 --> 00:27:15.320
but we did go for a while to part-time,

00:27:15.320 --> 00:27:21.320
but then it came then that you had to go full-time.

00:27:21.320 --> 00:27:24.320
So either that or you were actually left.

00:27:24.320 --> 00:27:27.320
So quite a few left then, didn't they?

00:27:27.320 --> 00:27:32.320
No, the few left them because that children there, because they didn't have nobody to look after them.

00:27:32.320 --> 00:27:38.320
But me and my friend stopped for a while and she left as well, so I stayed on.

00:27:39.320 --> 00:27:44.320
So how long were you in METOI for? Do you remember what time you left that? Left there?

00:27:44.320 --> 00:27:49.320
Well, we were made to run, it was 1973, see, so.

00:27:49.320 --> 00:27:51.320
That was from Fisher Price?

00:27:51.320 --> 00:28:01.320
No, no, from METOI. I can't remember what year we went from Fisher Price to METOI, I can't remember.

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:08.320
But I remember, well I looked at that bit, it was 1973 that we were made redundant in METOI.

00:28:08.320 --> 00:28:12.320
So I should have been about, I'd say nine or ten years there.

00:28:12.320 --> 00:28:13.320
Alright.

00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:16.320
Should have been, could be less, might.

00:28:16.320 --> 00:28:21.320
Okay, okay. Were you given any sort of training at all of what to do in METOI?

00:28:21.320 --> 00:28:22.320
No.

00:28:22.320 --> 00:28:23.320
Nothing at all?

00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:30.320
No, we just, they show you and then they stay by you to see that you were doing it right, like, see.

00:28:30.320 --> 00:28:35.320
Okay. And were you, did you have to wear a uniform at all in METOI either?

00:28:35.320 --> 00:28:36.320
No.

00:28:36.320 --> 00:28:42.320
Neither of them, okay. And was that because you were working with metal and smaller things, was that more dangerous?

00:28:42.320 --> 00:28:46.320
Or, or, you know, could you have an accident doing that, or?

00:28:46.320 --> 00:28:49.320
No, I don't think so, no.

00:28:49.320 --> 00:28:52.320
Because you know today, health and safety is important.

00:28:52.320 --> 00:28:53.320
Yes, yeah.

00:28:53.320 --> 00:28:55.320
Was that a factor then, or?

00:28:55.320 --> 00:29:01.320
No, I don't think it was so much then as it is now. No, it was.

00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:09.320
Okay. Would you say that, you know, that the working in METOI or in Fisher Price has affected your health in any way?

00:29:09.320 --> 00:29:11.320
Well, it didn't affect mine any of it.

00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:12.320
I don't think it has.

00:29:12.320 --> 00:29:13.320
I know.

00:29:13.320 --> 00:29:23.320
Right, okay. When you were working now in Fisher Price, did you work every day of the week, or was it just Monday to Friday, or what did you do?

00:29:23.320 --> 00:29:33.320
No, we worked, we, first I wanted us to come in on a Saturday, we were going in on a Saturday as well to have, what do you call it now?

00:29:33.320 --> 00:29:34.320
It was extra pay?

00:29:34.320 --> 00:29:41.320
Yeah. Oh, I can't remember, oh, you call it now. Yeah, we were having extra then by going in on a Saturday, see.

00:29:41.320 --> 00:29:43.320
That was something extra.

00:29:43.320 --> 00:29:46.320
Yes, a bit extra then, see. Yes.

00:29:46.320 --> 00:29:49.320
So there was shifts obviously in these factories.

00:29:49.320 --> 00:29:50.320
Oh, yes.

00:29:50.320 --> 00:29:55.320
What were the other shifts then? You know, you started at half past nine, did the other girls go off then?

00:29:55.320 --> 00:30:03.320
Oh, yes, they finished then, no, they, well, at half past nine, they were half past three, it was supposed to be then.

00:30:03.320 --> 00:30:07.320
They did have shifts there, they had afternoons and evenings there, see.

00:30:07.320 --> 00:30:08.320
Did they have night shifts as well?

00:30:08.320 --> 00:30:13.320
Yeah, they got night shifts at night, yes. Yeah, they got night shifts as well.

00:30:13.320 --> 00:30:21.320
So did you have bank holiday off, you know, would that have been a, did you work on a bank holiday at all? Christmas and?

00:30:21.320 --> 00:30:25.320
Oh, yeah, well, they'd re-hard them off, re-hard them off.

00:30:25.320 --> 00:30:30.320
