So both factories closed.

00:31:17.320 --> 00:31:18.320
Yeah.

00:31:18.320 --> 00:31:19.320
Ah, right, okay.

00:31:19.320 --> 00:31:20.320
Yeah.

00:31:20.320 --> 00:31:21.320
How did you feel about that? Did you feel sad that you were leaving?

00:31:21.320 --> 00:31:27.320
Yes, I did feel a bit sad because I did enjoy myself there and the money was handy as well.

00:31:27.320 --> 00:31:30.320
And was there sort of friendship with the other girls?

00:31:30.320 --> 00:31:33.320
Yes, there was a friendship for them as well, yeah.

00:31:33.320 --> 00:31:35.320
Have you kept in touch with some of the girls there?

00:31:35.320 --> 00:31:44.320
No, we haven't. Some of them I've seen don't go saying then, but most of them are gone now as well.

00:31:44.320 --> 00:31:49.320
So you didn't have a sort of retirement gift or?

00:31:49.320 --> 00:31:54.320
No, no, they didn't give us that, no. They didn't give us anything.

00:31:54.320 --> 00:32:00.320
And then did they have things like social club at all in METO, you know?

00:32:00.320 --> 00:32:01.320
No.

00:32:01.320 --> 00:32:02.320
No, nothing like that?

00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:03.320
No, we didn't have nothing like that.

00:32:03.320 --> 00:32:05.320
Football teams or cricket teams or anything?

00:32:05.320 --> 00:32:07.320
No, nothing like that, no.

00:32:07.320 --> 00:32:09.320
The bosses didn't bring people together at all?

00:32:09.320 --> 00:32:10.320
No.

00:32:10.320 --> 00:32:11.320
Did you see the bosses at all?

00:32:11.320 --> 00:32:12.320
No, we'd never seen them.

00:32:12.320 --> 00:32:14.320
Just the supervisors?

00:32:14.320 --> 00:32:19.320
And the girls was always there, we never saw the men.

00:32:19.320 --> 00:32:21.320
But the foreman was here?

00:32:21.320 --> 00:32:30.320
Yeah, he was around sometimes, yes. If there was any problems with the machines that they had, he'd come and have a look at it.

00:32:30.320 --> 00:32:33.320
So who mended the machines, would that be men?

00:32:33.320 --> 00:32:40.320
Well, yeah, we got men. Well, some of them, my young boys would come there as well and ought to do jobs there as well.

00:32:40.320 --> 00:32:48.320
Where did the other girls come from who worked there? Did they come from Goseinon, Lachau?

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:53.320
Well, when we were in the Fish and Price, they were coming from Port Talbot.

00:32:53.320 --> 00:32:59.320
Some of them were, yeah, from Port Talbot. They had the bus then coming from there, see.

00:32:59.320 --> 00:33:06.320
But they were all over the shop, really, but I know them from Port Talbot, because we were always together then on the line, like, see.

00:33:06.320 --> 00:33:08.320
The majority of them is Swansea.

00:33:08.320 --> 00:33:12.320
And the language was English, was it? Or was it Welsh at all?

00:33:12.320 --> 00:33:18.320
I didn't hear anybody speaking Welsh, most likely there was, there might, but I didn't hear anything.

00:33:18.320 --> 00:33:22.320
What about the Swansea girls? Were they, what were they like?

00:33:22.320 --> 00:33:26.320
Yes, they were all right, yeah. They were all right.

00:33:26.320 --> 00:33:29.320
I've heard stories about some of the Swansea girls. What do you think?

00:33:29.320 --> 00:33:38.320
They can be nasty, mind, but they're good to work with, mind. Yeah, they're good to work with, but don't cross her.

00:33:38.320 --> 00:33:43.320
What was their language like in the factory, you know? Is there a bit of blue language there?

00:33:43.320 --> 00:33:48.320
No, no, there was nothing like that there, fair does, no. Nothing like that there, no.

00:33:48.320 --> 00:33:56.320
Okay, all right. So, when you look back now at the days in the factory, what stays in your mind, you know?

00:33:56.320 --> 00:34:00.320
When you look back at, your memory goes back to those times.

00:34:00.320 --> 00:34:05.320
What are the most interesting or important things that you remember of that time?

